<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="299" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,466]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,369,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Etymology.</emphasis>
I dedicate this species to my husband, Paolo Volponi, a brilliant filmmaker and clearwing moth enthusiast, whose help and assistance in the field have been crucial in the studies of this and many other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[1343,1436,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sesiidae</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
